<p>The "yachting party" lounge by the Roblinsee and watch old captains sailing toy yachts like so many Peter Pans.</p>
<p>One old boy passes the afternoon by golfing along the lakeside.</p>
<p>4 pm.   Another appel (muster.) tea immediately afterwards.<br/>5 pm to 7 pm.   Classes again.<br/>7 pm.   Dinner.<br/>8 till 11.  usually Bridge &ndash; or at little parties in different rooms &ndash;<br/>Pictures every Saturday evening.</p>
<p>Thu. 9th May<br/>Ascension Thursday.   Go to church in the village with the Colonel and Captns Mingo and Lucas.   A splendid morning.   The limes are in full bloom and "Unter den Linden" (the road approaching the village) is now a leafy arcade.</p>
<p>The church is of mellow yellowed brick, spired, and stands in the centre of a large cobbled Marktplatz.   Service like High Anglican &ndash; a good choir and organ.</p>
